---
<BaseLayout title="CareCost Intelligence Sitemap | Tools, Guides, and States" description="Browse every estimator tool, state guide, care type comparison, policy page, and planning article to quickly find the senior care cost resource you need.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Sitemap</h1>
      <p class="note">Updated: Feb 2026. Use this page to navigate all tools, guides, and state pages.</p>
      <div class="tag">Last updated: Feb 2026</div>
      <div class="editorial-meta">Reviewed by CareCost Intelligence Editorial Team</div>
      <div class="author-box">
        <div class="author-title">Editorial review</div>
        <div class="author-meta">
          <div>
            <strong>CareCost Intelligence Editorial Team</strong>
            <p class="note">Navigation and taxonomy updated annually. Read our <a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial Policy</a>, <a href="/data-sources/">Data Sources</a>, or <a href="/contact/">report a correction</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chip-grid" style="margin-top: 12px;">
        <a class="chip" href="#sitemap-maintenance">How this page is updated</a>
        <a class="chip" href="#sitemap-core">Core pages</a>
        <a class="chip" href="#sitemap-guides">Guides</a>
        <a class="chip" href="#sitemap-states">State guides</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container card" id="sitemap-maintenance">
      <h2>How this page is updated</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Updated automatically during site builds to reflect new or removed pages.</li>
        <li>Cross-checked with the XML sitemap and robots.txt.</li>
        <li>Internal links are reviewed to prevent dead or orphaned pages.</li>
        <li>Corrections or missing links can be reported on the contact page.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="controls" style="margin-top: 12px;">
        <a class="btn secondary" href="/contact/">Report a link issue</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/sitemap.xml">XML sitemap</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container card">
      <h2>How to use this sitemap</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Start with the estimator to model a baseline range.</li>
        <li>Use state guides to validate local context before comparing quotes.</li>
        <li>Open guides for deeper pricing drivers and checklists.</li>
        <li>Return to the estimator to test a second scenario.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="note">If you are new to the site, begin with the planning checklist and glossary.</p>
      <div class="controls" style="margin-top: 12px;">
        <a class="btn secondary" href="/guides/cost-planning-checklist/">Planning checklist</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/glossary/">Glossary</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="sitemap-core">
    <div class="container card">
      <h2>Core pages</h2>
      <div class="grid-3">
        {corePages.map((page) => (
          <a class="tag" href={page.href}>{page.label}</a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="sitemap-guides">
    <div class="container card">
      <h2>Guides</h2>
      <div class="grid-2">
        {guidePages.map((page) => (
          <a class="tag" href={page.href}>{page.label}</a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="sitemap-states">
    <div class="container card">
      <h2>State cost guides</h2>
      <div class="grid-3">
        {statePages.map((page) => (
          <a class="tag" href={page.href}>{page.label}</a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
